In the foreground, place a yellow tent perched atop a rocky outcrop, with a soft, warm glow emanating from within, creating a sense of comfort and shelter amidst the wild landscape. To achieve this breathtaking shot, use a wide-angle lens such as the Nikon AF-S NIKKOR 14-24mm f/2.8G ED, which will enable you to capture the expansive sky, the towering mountain, and the foreground detail of the tent. Set your focal length at 14mm, allowing for a wide field of view to encompass the entire scene. For this night photography scene, utilize low-light techniques and a long exposure to capture the brilliance of the stars and the subtle glow from the tent. Set your aperture to f/2.8 and use a high ISO, around 3200, to maximize the sensitivity of the camera's sensor to light. Utilize a sturdy tripod and a shutter speed of 20-25 seconds to ensure the sharpness of the stars and the landscape. In terms of lighting style, employ natural ambient lighting from the stars and the tent's faint glow. The tent light should provide a gentle, warm contrast to the cool tones of the snowy mountain and the night sky, adding depth and interest to the composition. During post-processing, adjust the white balance to accurately represent the coolness of the night and the warmth of the tent light. Enhance the contrast and clarity to bring out the texture of the rocks and the details of the distant snow-capped mountain. By following these guidelines, you'll create a captivating image that conveys the beauty and tranquility of a starlit night in a remote, majestic landscape. ‚Äîv 5
